Welcome to CD!

elsaelisa09:

Please help me

It’s very rare that symptoms (like the error message you posted) have a singular root cause. Also, for a moment, put yourself in the shoes of someone attempting to answer the question - we don’t know you or your team at all, we don’t know what you’re trying to accomplish, we don’t know what already know or where your knowledge gaps are… All this adds up to… you’ll need to provide more detail for getting effective help online.

The general way I tell my students to structure their questions:

  1. What is your end goal? If all goes well, what do you hope to accomplish?
  2. What method did you choose to achieve the end goal? What steps have you tried already?
  3. What did you expect to happen? What did you actually see?

These questions are designed to get you in the mindset of the scientific method - form hypothesis, run experiment, interpret result, repeat.
